content: Have had since she was 5 now almost 8 still loves it

Amazing, except i have to rotate the parts for my son, it's too difficult for him. And my son wishes it had trees for the saw to cut and dirt for the shovels/loaders to dig!!! and he wishes food could come out of the fridge. (He's almost three) lol
Would give this a 10 if I could!!! Great for my 2 1\2 yr old grandson and will even play myself on my many plane rides to give my grandson other ideas of what to build.
Can't rotate any of the pieces. Money wasted.
replyContent:
Hello,
Here is a little help to rotate:
- Imagine that there is an invisible circle around the object you want to rotate.
- With two fingers touch the invisible circle (without your fingers touching the object) 
- Move your fingers to rotate
